content: There's randomly generated, then there's auto lose situations that make no sense at all. As an avid RPG gamer and rouge like style gamer I am used to harsh penalty's upon a mistake but this game legitimately has little to no logic behind some of the outcomes. Point being I purposely exited areas without searching, ignored decisions but clicking any random option without reading, skipped all trader camps and gave into all bandit demands and guess what, that run was the furthest got.

While DR2C's pros far outweigh its cons,such cons are grave. Movement is horrible, "slow" zombies that are faster than YOU in hardmodes,*THIS SIEGE IS OVER* messages that forces you to take your hand from the clunky movement pad to click OK, often making you take a hit or kill you, fake difficulty related to bad and random events and there's too much zombies on some stages that a mid-range, 4GB Ram, 2GHz octacore LAGS! Worth it for the Black Friday's 1 buck, wouldn't pay 10$. Addicting though!

Seemed like game over but the dog did the impossible, broke through the crowd of zombies and ran outside to escape. Happy/sad moment with the dog being the sole survivor but hey it's my 1st win 😂

This is a Retro styled Top down Rogue-Lite RPG.It puts you in a randomly generated party of survivors where you take control of either a Random or personalised character to reach Canada.It has great decision system which affects your playstyle drastically.It is endlessly replayable as each character has their own positives and negatives which you can mix and match based on your liking.There are a lot of deep mechanics at play that it doesn't tell you in begining.This is worth every penny.

I will list a couple of things I would like to see in later updates. 1. multiplayer, I would like it if you could play with a friend if they had it on their mobile device, and they could mix with their characters. 2. it would be really cool if they added a couple of bosses in this game, we could have a separate mode for bosses like "boss mode" or something like that. 3. I would like more customization with our characters, and maybe we could find exclusive things as we play the game, and just be able to find different customization in shops while we're looting. 4. I would like to be able to craft and make new weapons by combining different weapons, it would be cool to be able to see in your own car too and be able to customize things inside, maybe you could find posters and stuff to put in your car while you're looting. maybe we could also make food by combining food but it would make us more full. I see all the updates you guys do and I really like that you're very active on this game too, which is something I like about this game too. so these were some of my ideas, thanks for reading this review, and just think about my recommendations and see if they'd be a good idea. I also don't get why this game isn't more popular it's just so good. so please just think about my ideas and that would be great:D I also have another thing so this is an edit: I wish choices mattered more. so for example one could be that you turned down someone and didn't accept them into the group, then maybe later in the game they would have a whole team of bandits and you would have to fight them. so that would make the choices matter more and it would be a more memorable story with making memorable friends and enemies, it would be cool too if sometimes there would be bandits while you're looting stuff too, so it wouldn't be just zombies. edit: also minigames would be cool, and so would sidequests that occur between other people from outside your group and sidequests from within your group members. keep up the great work guys.

There was a lot of promise, but the farther in you get, the more frustrating the controls are,  and every other second a player catched him/herself noticing all the things that could of made the game better, more enjoyable, less of a pain to play, and more intriguing. This game, even from the very beginning, was missing a few core attributes that are essential to a more retro feel rpg. 1 ,The game has to be fun, and with zombies, you constantly want a hack and slash or satisfying kills. 2, a good story , with characters fhat grow and have personality. Ghe game prides itself in the generated story feature, but with that come the liss of, relatable characters, quality story, and a reasonable or understandable plot, a drive of the main questions.  Why are we here Whats going on, how do we stop it How do we survive. It missed that, snd gameplay did not make up for it, yes i agree this is a phenomenal mobile game and amazingly large for its file size. But... its still kinda boring and not enjoyable. The third issue is that when you reach the border to Canada the framerate will drop to around 2-4 fps on my Pixel XL until most of the zombies are cleared out.   My review would immediately change to 5 stars if the crashing issues were fixed. The FPS issue at the end would be nice to have fixed as well, but it's not as important of an issue. This game is, quite honestly, one of my favorite games in recent memory. The randomness of it can be a little brutal and fun-killing at times, but it makes being able to finish the game that much more satisfying.   Tips for beginners: - ALWAYS be looting - The game jokes about chairs and furniture being useful; they actually are your best weapons! - You can get a lot of zombo points right of the bat by talking to the chicken in the unlocks section. Use these to get some early upgrades to custom characters (NOTE: Initially you can only carry 10 zombo points at once, and if you talk to the chicken when your points are full you'll get NOTHING) - Open all the toilets you can. The 1 gas you get from them seems silly, but something absolutely magical happens when you open enough of them.
